# Workflow Standards

## Golden Path (Spec Kit + ECC)

Follow this sequence for feature work to reduce rework:

1. `/speckit-clarify` to resolve ambiguity in `spec.md` before planning.
2. `/speckit-plan` to produce technical plan and data model.
3. `/speckit-tasks` to generate executable task breakdown.
4. `/speckit-analyze` to detect consistency, coverage, and constitution issues.
5. `/speckit-checklist` to generate requirement-quality checklists (not implementation tests).
6. Run Spec Test Bundle:
   - `/speckit-test-coverage` for requirement-to-test mapping coverage
   - `/speckit-test-gaps` to detect uncovered requirements
   - `/speckit-test-plan` to define execution strategy before implementation/testing
   - `/speckit-test-generate` when test scaffolding is required
7. Execute implementation only after steps 1-6 are complete and reviewed.

## Operational Rules

- Do not skip `/speckit-clarify` unless user explicitly accepts higher rework risk.
- Run `/speckit-analyze` only after `tasks.md` exists and is complete.
- Treat constitution conflicts found by `/speckit-analyze` as CRITICAL blockers.
- Run `/speckit-test-coverage` and `/speckit-test-gaps` after checklist generation as minimum testability gate.
- Use `/speckit-test-plan` before coding when feature scope is medium/large or cross-module.
- Use `/speckit-test-generate` to bootstrap tests from accepted acceptance criteria.
- Keep all implementation work traceable to `tasks.md`.
- Use feature branches for Spec Kit flows; avoid executing planning and tasks on non-feature branches.

## Definition of Ready for Coding

Coding starts only when all conditions are met:

- `spec.md`, `plan.md`, and `tasks.md` are present for the active feature.
- Clarifications are integrated into spec.
- No unresolved CRITICAL analysis findings remain.
- Checklist coverage exists for relevant requirement-quality areas.
- Spec Test Bundle minimum gate is passed:
  - `/speckit-test-coverage` completed
  - `/speckit-test-gaps` completed with no blocking gaps
- For medium/large features, `/speckit-test-plan` is completed before coding.
